Definition:
 DPL, or Debian Project Leader, is a official reprentative of the Debian
 Project. DPL defines the vision of the Debian Project and reprents Debian to
 the external world.
 .
 DPL is chosen by election each year where all Debian Developers (DDs) are
 eligible to vote. DPL may delegate responsibility to other DDs and may nominate
 DDs to the certain positions like the the Project Secretary etc.
 .
 Also see: <http://www.debian.org/devel/leader>
